text: Mohammad Ali Khan (born 6 September 1998) is a Pakistani cricketer. He made his first-class debut for Multan in the 2018–19 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy on 1 September 2018. He was the joint-leading wicket-taker for Multan in the tournament, with twenty-two dismissals in five matches. Prior to his first- class debut, he was part of Pakistan's squad for the 2018 Under-19 Cricket World Cup. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Pakistani cricketers Category:Multan cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Southern Punjab (Pakistan) cricketers
